title: Pingtan Marine names Mr  LiMing Yung as CFO
content:
Pingtan Marine  PME  1 1   announces the appointment of Mr  LiMing Yung  Michael   the Company s Senior Vice President as Chief Financial Officer effective December 5  2019 
Mr  Yung will be succeeding Mr  Roy Yu  who tendered his resignation effective December 5  2019 
Mr  Yung has been Pingtan s Senior Vice President since 2015  Prior to joining Pingtan  he was the Vice President of Citicorp Investment  Senior Vice President of UBS Paine Webber and Managing Director of Terra Nova Natural Resources

title: U S  stocks mixed at close of trade  Dow Jones Industrial Average down 0 16
content:
Investing com   U S  stocks were mixed after the close on Wednesday  as gains in the Oil   Gas  Basic Materials and Financials sectors led shares higher while losses in the Healthcare  Consumer Services and Industrials sectors led shares lower 
At the close in NYSE  the Dow Jones Industrial Average declined 0 16   while the S P 500 index added 0 11   and the NASDAQ Composite index climbed 0 14  
The best performers of the session on the Dow Jones Industrial Average were  Chevron  Corporation  NYSE CVX   which rose 1 35  or 1 42 points to trade at 106 50 at the close  Meanwhile   Caterpillar  Inc  NYSE CAT  added 1 08  or 1 07 points to end at 100 36 and Merck   Company Inc  NYSE MRK  was up 1 03  or 0 65 points to 63 94 in late trade 
The worst performers of the session were Walt  Disney  Company  NYSE DIS   which fell 2 15  or 2 41 points to trade at 109 66 at the close   Boeing Co   NYSE BA  declined 1 25  or 2 31 points to end at 183 18 and Intel Corporation  NASDAQ INTC  was down 0 99  or 0 36 points to 36 01 
The top performers on the S P 500 were NVIDIA Corporation  NASDAQ NVDA  which rose 17 83  to 121 29   Electronic Arts Inc   NASDAQ EA  which was up 12 65  to settle at 108 16 and  Coty Inc   NYSE COTY  which gained 11 86  to close at 19 95 
The worst performers were Frontier Communications Corporation  NASDAQ FTR  which was down 9 79  to 1 29 in late trade  Priceline com Incorporated  NASDAQ PCLN  which lost 4 54  to settle at 1824 41 and Allergan Plc  NYSE AGN  which was down 3 69  to 229 72 at the close 
The top performers on the NASDAQ Composite were ITUS Corp  NASDAQ ITUS  which rose 47 83  to 1 700   MannKind Corp   NASDAQ MNKD  which was up 42 86  to settle at 1 600 and  Neuralstem  Inc  NASDAQ CUR  which gained 36 18  to close at 3 9900 
The worst performers were Rocket Fuel Inc  NASDAQ FUEL  which was down 35 28  to 3 210 in late trade  Concordia International Corp  NASDAQ CXRX  which lost 30 29  to settle at 1 45 and  Pingtan Marine  Enterprise Ltd  NASDAQ PME  which was down 28 22  to 2 950 at the close 
Rising stocks outnumbered declining ones on the New York Stock Exchange by 2045 to 1146 and 49 ended unchanged  on the Nasdaq Stock Exchange  1336 rose and 1166 declined  while 99 ended unchanged 
Shares in NVIDIA Corporation  NASDAQ NVDA  rose to all time highs  rising 17 83  or 18 35 to 121 29  Shares in Frontier Communications Corporation  NASDAQ FTR  fell to 5 year lows  down 9 79  or 0 14 to 1 29  Shares in Electronic Arts Inc  NASDAQ EA  rose to all time highs  gaining 12 65  or 12 15 to 108 16  
The CBOE Volatility Index  which measures the implied volatility of S P 500 options  was up 1 71  to 10 13 
Gold Futures for June delivery was up 0 31  or 3 76 to  1219 86 a troy ounce  Elsewhere in commodities trading  Crude oil for delivery in June rose 3 16  or 1 45 to hit  47 33 a barrel  while the July Brent oil contract rose 3 00  or 1 46 to trade at  50 19 a barrel
